In case of Iron deficiency anaemia, Oral Iron therapy should not be stopped even after the patient achieves a haemoglobin of &gt;12 mg/dL. After the haemoglobin target has been reached, iron supplementation should be continued for another 6 months in order to rebuild the depleted reserves.<br />
&nbsp;
<p><em><strong>Reference</strong>: Harrison&#39;s Principles of Internal Medicine, 21st edition, Page no 748-452.</em></p>
